by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-6-406, is amended by deleting the
section and substituting:
Each public senior high school shall provide official recruiting representatives of
the military forces of this state and the United States access to the public senior high
school:
(1) At least once a month during student lunch periods for the purpose of
informing students of educational and career opportunities available in the
military; and
(2) At least once every other month in which school is in session to
provide further information about the military forces for students who have
expressed interest in the military forces and who would like more information.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2025, the public welfare requiring it.
